I have created the `coworker-memory-generator` scripts in both PowerShell and Bash to support the generation of daily, monthly, yearly, and global memory summaries as requested.

### Created Files
- `coworker/scripts/coworker-memory-generator.ps1`
- `coworker/scripts/coworker-memory-generator.sh`

These scripts support the following usage:
- `daily`: Wraps the existing daily generator (default).
- `monthly`: Aggregates all daily memories for a given month and generates a summary.
- `yearly`: Aggregates all monthly memories for a given year and generates a summary.
- `all`: Aggregates all yearly memories (or monthly if yearly are missing) and generates a global summary.

